The paper deals with mechanism design in the context of crowdsourcing markets, which is a topic that falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of submodular utility functions, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The design of the mechanism involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with economic aspects of crowdsourcing markets, which falls under the category of computational economics (cs.EC).
